    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u><strong>Overview</strong></u></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Tumble Track is a multi player climbing game meant to frustrate even the most dedicated gamers. It can be played alone or with up to 3 friends (4 people total). It has multiple difficulties from Baby mode, Easy mode, Normal mode, and Intended Mode. When playing with friends choose to work together or shoot one another off the course. The game is currently in early access so if you want to shape what it will become please join the discord or leave suggestions on the store page!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong><u>Developer commentary</u></strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >As you travel your journey up the random objects on the first island there are comments from the developers to encourage you to continue your climb. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u><strong>Difficulty system</strong></u></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Baby mode</strong> - This difficulty has the most amount of check points and the obstacles are so easy its boring. Having any achievements related to this difficulty should bring shame to your family name.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Easy mode</strong> - Has slightly less check points and the obstacles are not to crazy.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Normal mode</strong> - Just a normal game mode with a fair amount of check points.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Intended mode</strong> - The difficulty system was added from demand from the community, however the developers didn't want to add it. Which is why there is &quot;intended mode&quot; which is the way that the developer intended on how the game should be played.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
